CONVERSATION TITLE: Become a work-place ready engineer at TEDI-London
CONTENT:
Hi Soundarya!


I'm the Dean of The Engineering & Design Institute London (TEDI-London) - a new, engineering-specialist higher education provider in Canada Water. If you're considering a new career move, I thought you might be interested in learning more about our hands-on, project-based Global Design Engineering degree programmes and how they can help you enhance your professional skillset.


The engineering industry is crucial when it comes to solving global challenges such as food shortage, climate change, and inequality. As an engineer, you could make a real-world difference, whilst also working in a fast-paced and innovative industry where teamwork and problem-solving are at the heart of every project. With fantastic career prospects and a broad range of roles and sectors to work in, becoming an engineer has never been so exciting.


Studying a degree at TEDI-London will help you build a professional project portfolio, develop important theoretical and workplace skills, and network with key industry employers.


If you're interested, come along to our next open day to discover our state-of-the-art campus facilities and learn more about Global Design Engineering.


Hope to see you there,

Professor Judy Raper

CONTENT: Hi Soundarya,   I hope you are keeping well. :)  I wanted to invite you to a free virtual careers event we are running on Wednesday 21st April 2021 (12:30pm until 4:30pm), focused on tech graduate roles and internships in the UK! So far the event's exciting exhibitors include Analsys Mason, REPL, VMWare, Ekimetrics, Virgin, GFT, Alacrity, Capita, Willmott Dixon, Softcat, Alfa Systems, KPMG, Barclays and SLC. CONVERSATION TITLE: Earn an MSc in Artificial Intelligence online
CONTENT:
Hi Soundarya,


Hope you‚Äôre well! I‚Äôm a course adviser for the University of Hull. Based on your experience and interests, I think you may be an excellent candidate for our online MSc in Artificial Intelligence.


Our part-time, online MSc can be taken over two years whilst you continue to work. You‚Äôll be guided by our expert academics and get to connect and engage with like-minded peers across the globe.


On this MSc, you can expect to:


¬∑      Hone the skills you need to identify and implement AI, Machine Learning, and Deep Learning techniques, tools, and algorithms to solve problems

¬∑      Learn how to express your ideas to non-specialists, and how to present the results of complex AI solutions

¬∑      Explore the wider contexts within which AI sits, and address the cultural, ethical, social, and legal implications of fair AI use

¬∑      Use advanced research methods and progress your understanding of business models and management to contextualise your output. 


If you feel this course might be a good fit for you, please submit an enquiry. After that, either myself or a fellow course adviser will be in touch to discuss the programme and go over the application process.


I look forward to hearing from you.


Victoria Zuber

University of Hull Online

CONVERSATION TITLE: Join us at ICWES18 online 1-3 Sept - Registration now open
CONTENT:
Dear Soundarya,


The 18th International Conference of Women Engineers and Scientists will be hosted online by the University of Warwick 1-3 September 2021, and we are pleased to announce that registration is now OPEN!

 

Established in 1964 and hosted every 3 years, ICWES is the flagship event of the International Network of Women Engineers and Scientists (INWES). ICWES attracts in excess of 500 engineers and scientists from all over the world, providing a unique opportunity to exchange information on their work, careers and offers a plethora of opportunities to discuss innovative technologies in the 21st century across the engineering, science and technological professions, allowing unrivalled networking with colleagues in business, academia and government.

 

ICWES18 will be structured around the theme ‚ÄòGlobal Humanitarian Challenges‚Äô covering topics such as climate change, global health and pandemics, renewable energy, sustainable cities, water and sanitation and natural/man-made disasters. The conference will also focus on the role of education and training of women in tackling societal challenges. Click here for video.
